About this hotel

A 5-minute walk from the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square, this refined hotel in a 14th-century building is 1 km from the 12th-century Koutoubia Mosque and 7 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 1:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    PIEvents And Co3 weeks ago on Google
    5/5
    You will find so many Dars or Riads in Marrakech that you will not be able to choose one of them at first sight, even reading many reviews from different platform. So during our trip we stayed in 4 different hotel to compare their offer. 
    You will find so many Dars or Riads in Marrakech that you will not be able to choose one of them at first sight, even reading many reviews from different platform. So during our trip we stayed in 4 different hotel to compare their offer.
    Dar Justo was the last one we stayed in and we were not disappointed. The place is so big that you can hold a wedding with more than 70 people. The staff was friendly and helpful : it is quite difficult to know where you are because Marrakech is a labyrinth, so a little bit of help is necessary. And behind the walls, are hidden some treasures you can't imagine.
    To find the places, and we say it for almost all the riads and Dars, you'd better find the right taxi man, this way you will not waste your time finding your hotel.
    The room we stayed in was typical Moroccan. There was a walkin shower with earth ware tiles and tadelakt wall finishing in the bedroom. The entire hotel has been decorated with the most refined art crafts. The manager told us that the wood carved doors were built in Spain.
    Every morning, the staff served us a wonderful breakfast with Moroccan specialties. It was a buffet style with fresh goods and fruits. The night, you can enjoy a dinner at the restaurant.
    Little advice: avoid the Ramadan time. Because there are less tourists, Moroccan in the streets are hungry (financially too) and they are ready to sale you anything they can. We ended up giving a lot of money to poor people .

    Dar Justo Riad is a hidden gem in the medina of Marrakech. In case you didnt know, a riad is a traditional Moroccan house or palace with an interior garden or courtyard divided into quarters with a central fountain. This house was converted into a beautiful hotel, decorated with very good taste, with many cozy spaces where you can read and enjoy your favorite drink. There are shelves with many books in the common areas. It has a terrace where you can see the Koutoubia mosque, which is illuminated at night. You can also see the snow-capped Atlas mountains. You can also hear the call to pray from the nearby mosque. For us it was a kind of call to meditate.
    Every single detail of the hotel is for your rest and enjoyment. Riad rooms not only have a number but also a name of a famous artist as a tribute. The room was spotless and really comfortable. Breakfast was really good, too, and was included. The reception staff was very friendly and helpful, and they immediately made us feel welcome.
    In Dar Justo Riad you will feel like a real pasha.

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakeshs original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    A 5-minute walk from the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square, this refined hotel in a 14th-century building is 1 km from the 12th-century Koutoubia Mosque and 7 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    Relaxed, warmly decorated rooms feature Wi-Fi, flat-screens and safes. Suites living areas; some feature loft bedrooms and/or elaborate woodwork.

    Breakfast is available. There's also rooftop restaurant with city views. Other amenities include lounges and a hammam, as well as a courtyard with a pool and sitting areas.
